The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the market close.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 1.3 percent to 20,434.58. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 1.7 percent to 2,734.43.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell 3.7 percent to $1.03
after crude slumped in  New York .  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, dropped 4.4 percent to 65 cents after
copper declined in New York.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, slid 3.5 percent to 55 cents.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, slid 3.2 percent to $30.39.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
